  "description": "This cluster of papers explores the concepts of media framing, agenda setting, and mediatization within the field of communication research. It delves into the influence of news media on public perceptions, the role of journalism culture, and the analysis of content in mass communication. The cluster also examines the impact of digital journalism and cultural production on shaping news narratives and political communication.",
